<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Statute lims:pit-date="2002-12-31" lims:lastAmendedDate="2002-12-31" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431361" lims:id="431361" bill-origin="commons" bill-type="govt-public" xml:lang="en" in-force="yes" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431362" lims:id="431362"><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431363" lims:id="431363">An Act respecting Sir John A. Macdonald Day and Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day</LongTitle><ShortTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431364" lims:id="431364" status="official">Sir John A. Macdonald Day and the Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day Act</ShortTitle><RunningHead lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431365" lims:id="431365">Sir John A. Macdonald Day and the Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day</RunningHead><BillHistory lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431366" lims:id="431366"><Stages lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431367" lims:id="431367" stage="assented-to"><Date><YYYY>2002</YYYY><MM>3</MM><DD>21</DD></Date></Stages><Stages lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" stage="consolidation"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></Stages></BillHistory><Chapter lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431369" lims:id="431369"><ConsolidatedNumber official="no">S-10.4</ConsolidatedNumber><AnnualStatuteId revised-statute="no"><AnnualStatuteNumber>2</AnnualStatuteNumber><YYYY>2002</YYYY></AnnualStatuteId></Chapter></Identification><Introduction lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431370" lims:id="431370"><Preamble lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431371" lims:id="431371" salutation="no"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431372" lims:id="431372" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431373" lims:id="431373">Preamble</MarginalNote><Text>WHEREAS Sir John Alexander Macdonald was born on January 11, 1815;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431374" lims:id="431374" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>AND WHEREAS he was one of the founders of Confederation;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431375" lims:id="431375" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>AND WHEREAS he was the first Prime Minister of Canada;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431376" lims:id="431376" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>AND WHEREAS Sir Wilfrid Laurier was born on November 20, 1841;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431377" lims:id="431377" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>AND WHEREAS he was Prime Minister of Canada from 1896 to 1911;</Text></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431378" lims:id="431378" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>AND WHEREAS he was the first Prime Minister of French ancestry and a fervent promoter of national unity;</Text></Provision></Preamble><Enacts lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431379" lims:id="431379"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431380" lims:id="431380" language-align="no" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>Her Majesty, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate and House of Commons of Canada, enacts as follows:</Text></Provision></Enacts></Introduction><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431381" lims:id="431381"><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431382" lims:id="431382" level="1"><TitleText>Short Title</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:lastAmendedDate="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431383" lims:id="431383"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431384" lims:id="431384">Short title</MarginalNote><Label>1</Label><Text>This Act may be cited as the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="S-10.4">Sir John A. Macdonald Day and the Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day Act</XRefExternal>.</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431385" lims:id="431385" level="1"><TitleText>Sir John A. Macdonald Day</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:lastAmendedDate="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431386" lims:id="431386"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431387" lims:id="431387">Sir John A. Macdonald Day</MarginalNote><Label>2</Label><Text>Throughout Canada, in each and every year, the 11th day of January shall be known under the name of "Sir John A. Macdonald Day".</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431388" lims:id="431388" level="1"><TitleText>Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:lastAmendedDate="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431389" lims:id="431389"><MarginalNote lims:inforce-start-date="2002-12-31" lims:fid="431390" lims:id="431390">Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day</MarginalNote><Label>3</Label><Text>Throughout Canada, in each and every year, the twentieth day of November shall be known under the name of "Sir Wilfrid Laurier Day".</Text></Section></Body></Statute>